1
00:00:00,270 --> 00:00:10,879
The more I can learn about other people, their ideas, interests, viewpoints, the better job I can do in giving them the merchandise and service they want and will buy.

2
00:00:12,350 --> 00:00:17,679
Here are a few simple do's to help make your social environment first class.

3
00:00:17,679 --> 00:00:19,119
1.

4
00:00:19,390 --> 00:00:21,760
Do circulate in new groups.

5
00:00:21,950 --> 00:00:28,639
Restricting your social environment to the same small group produces boredom, dullness, dissatisfaction.

6
00:00:28,910 --> 00:00:36,879
Equally important, remember that your success-building program requires that you become an expert in understanding people.

7
00:00:37,310 --> 00:00:46,639
Trying to learn all there is to know about people by studying one small group is like trying to master mathematics by reading one short book.

8
00:00:47,470 --> 00:00:52,480
make new friends, join new organizations, enlarge your social orbit.

9
00:00:52,830 --> 00:01:01,040
Then too, variety in people, like variety in anything else, adds spice to life and gives it a broader dimension.

10
00:01:01,150 --> 00:01:03,040
It's good mind food.

11
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:05,359
2.

12
00:01:05,629 --> 00:01:09,280
Do select friends who have views different from your own.

13
00:01:09,390 --> 00:01:13,679
In this modern age, the narrow individual hasn't much future.

14
00:01:13,869 --> 00:01:20,480
Responsibility and positions of importance gravitate to the person who is able to see both sides.

15
00:01:20,750 --> 00:01:26,159
If you're a Republican, make sure you have some friends who are Democrats, and vice versa.

16
00:01:26,430 --> 00:01:29,119
Get to know people of different religious faiths.

17
00:01:29,230 --> 00:01:34,879
Associate with opposites, but just be sure they are persons with real potential.

18
00:01:34,879 --> 00:01:37,119
3.

19
00:01:37,470 --> 00:01:42,159
Do select friends who stand above petty, unimportant things.

20
00:01:42,430 --> 00:01:53,200
Folks who are more concerned with the square footage of your home or the appliances you have or don't have than with your ideas and your conversation are inclined to be petty.

21
00:01:53,629 --> 00:01:56,080
Guard your psychological environment.

22
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:59,600
Select friends who are interested in positive things.

23
00:01:59,790 --> 00:02:02,720
Friends who really do want to see you succeed.

24
00:02:03,070 --> 00:02:07,200
Find friends who breathe encouragement into your plans and ideals.

25
00:02:07,390 --> 00:02:11,760
If you don't, if you select petty thinkers as your close friends,

26
00:02:11,869 --> 00:02:15,520
you'll gradually develop into a petty thinker yourself.

27
00:02:17,629 --> 00:02:20,159
We're a poison-conscious nation.

28
00:02:20,350 --> 00:02:22,240
Body poison, that is.

29
00:02:22,670 --> 00:02:26,320
Every restaurateur is on guard against food poisoning.

30
00:02:26,510 --> 00:02:31,200
Just a couple of cases of it, and his patrons won't come near his place.

31
00:02:31,550 --> 00:02:35,919
We've got tons of laws to protect the public against hundreds of body poisons.
